Package: overcoverage2
Type: Package
Title: Capture-Recapture Hidden Markov Models for Register-Based
        Population Inference
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Lucy", "Brown", role = "aut"),
    person("Eleni", "Matechou", role = "aut"),
    person("Bruno", "Santos", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "brdsantos@fc.ul.pt"),
    person("Eleonora", "Mussino", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Implements a capture-recapture hidden Markov model framework for
    register-based inference of population size and dynamics, allowing false
    positive and false negative observation error, temporary emigration, and
    multiple interacting registers. Provides maximum likelihood estimation and
    uncertainty quantification via the Bag of Little Bootstraps, with support
    for covariates and unobserved heterogeneity to study overcoverage in
    population registers.
